Initial commit: Airport Runway Management System

CSE123 Spring 2026 project. A real-time airport simulation built around
two from-scratch data structures: a binary max-heap for priority dispatch
of pending flights, and a singly-linked-list FIFO queue for per-runway
service lines and the global flight log.

Layered architecture:
  - src/ds/     : MaxHeap<T>, Queue<T>           (data structures)
  - src/model/  : Flight, Runway                 (application model)
  - src/        : Scheduler, main (CLI), bench   (composition + UI)
  - tests/      : 63-case hand-written test suite (no exceptions)

Three binaries produced by build.bat:
  - run_tests.exe     full test suite (63/63 passing)
  - runway_sim.exe    interactive CLI simulator
  - runway_bench.exe  perf benchmarks at n = 10^2 .. 10^6

Documentation in docs/:
  - final_report.md       full project write-up
  - study_guide.md        viva preparation, all things-to-do with answers
  - benchmark_results.txt empirical perf numbers
  - demo_scenario.txt     canned 13-line CLI script for the demo
